g.text: • Can reach the first rung (base case)
• Can always reach the next rung
Base Case: Prove P(n₀) is true
Assume P(k) is true for some k ≥ n₀
P(n) is true for all n ≥ n₀ ∎
Assume P(j) is true for ALL j
using ANY or ALL of P(n₀), P(n₀+1), ..., P(k)
• Use any previous cases P(j) where j ≤ k
• Break down P(k+1) into smaller subproblems
P(n) is true for all n ≥ n₀ ∎
